
# GASD Enhancement Proposal (GEP) Template

```text
GEP: XXXX
Title: <Short descriptive title>
Author: <Name(s)>
Status: Draft | Review | Accepted | Rejected
Type: Standards Track | Informational | Process
Created: YYYY-MM-DD
Replaces: <optional>
Requires: <optional>
```

---

# Abstract

Provide a short summary of the proposal.

Explain **what change is being proposed and why it matters** in 2–4 sentences.

---

# Motivation

Describe the problem this proposal solves.

Include:

* current limitation or issue
* why the change is needed
* who benefits from the change

---

# Specification

Describe the **proposed change clearly and precisely**.

This section should contain enough detail for implementers.

Examples may include:

* grammar changes
* new keywords or constructs
* validation rules
* changes to system behavior

Example structure:

```
Change:
Add a new GASD construct called <ExampleConstruct>.

Syntax:
ExampleConstruct <name>

Rules:
- Must appear inside <parent construct>
- Name must be unique within scope
```

---

# Rationale

Explain the design decisions.

Include:

* why this approach was chosen
* alternative designs considered
* trade-offs or limitations

---

# Backwards Compatibility

Describe whether the proposal affects existing GASD files or tooling.

Possible cases:

* fully backward compatible
* partially compatible with migration
* breaking change

If breaking, provide a migration approach.

---

# Reference Implementation (Optional)

If available, reference implementation details such as:

* grammar updates
* parser changes
* AST changes
* validation rules

Example:

```
ANTLR rule: exampleConstruct
AST node: ExampleConstructNode
```

---

# Test Plan

Describe how the proposal will be validated.

Examples:

Acceptance Test

```
AT-EXAMPLE-001
Valid ExampleConstruct parses successfully
```

Regression Test

```
RT-EXAMPLE-001
Existing constructs still parse correctly
```

Negative Test

```
NT-EXAMPLE-001
ExampleConstruct without name fails validation
```

---

# Traceability

Link the proposal to specification and implementation artifacts.

Example:

```
Requirement: REQ-EX-001
Spec Section: 4.3 ExampleConstruct
Grammar: exampleConstruct rule
Parser: ExampleConstructNode
Tests: AT-EX-001
```

---

